recommend check-in on the pre-existing copyForwards RED (its own dedicated pass, out of this turn's scope) and on the strategic question answered in prose this same turn: build a small real |- parser prototype next, before any reference-grade documentation or beginner-tutorial writing starts, since documenting a compiler that does not yet parse anything would mean writing aspirational pseudocode this tree's own docs-implementation-sync rule already warns against.
